Commission (AHRC), was forced into a jeep, handcuffed and blindfolded. He was reportedly 
taken to an unknown location and interrogated by up to eight men who threatened to kill him if 
he continued to maintain contact with representatives of the AHRC. Several members of the local 
community who actively assisted representatives from the AHRC have reportedly received 
similar threats. 
