<p><b>Summary 
</b></p>
<p><b>executions;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged excessive use of force resulting in killings when Israeli security forces opened fire 
against protesters. According to the information received, on 5 June 2011, Israeli troops opened 
fire killing between 30 and 40 protestors.  It is alleged that the protestors threw rocks and 
Motolov cocktails and attempted to damage the border fence. In response, the Israeli Defence 
Force opened fire on the protestors. Further, on 15 May 2011, at least 12 protestors were killed 
when Israeli Defense Forces opened fire on Palestinians at Israel&#8223;s borders with Lebanon and 
</p>
<p>Syria, as well as in the West Bank and Gaza Strip. 
</p>
