activist, was summoned via a telephone call for interrogation by the State Security Police on 7 
June 2011. He was allegedly arrested and accused of insulting the Bahraini and Saudi Arabian 
ruling families on his Twitter account. On 12 June 2011, Mr. Abul appeared before the Kuwaiti 
General Prosecution Office on state security charges, including &#8220;damaging the country&#8223;s 
interests&#8221; and &#8220;severing political relationship with brotherly countries&#8221;. Mr. Abul  was held in 
</p>
