<p>Alleged acts of violence and intimidation against human rights defenders. According to the 
information received, on 14 June 2011, private guards opened fire and beat protestors who had 
set up camp outside the Central Mindanao University (CMU).  The guards had reportedly been 
hired by the CMU. Mr. Billy Jardin, Mr. Gregorio Santillan and Mr. Larry de Vera reportedly 
received gunshot wounds and were hospitalised. The guards allegedly beat many of the protesters 
including Mr. Wenni Loable, Mr. Jos&#233; Benemerito and Ms. Marilou Fortin, who were seriously 
injured as a result.  The aforementioned human rights defenders are members of the Buffalo-
Tamaraw-Limus (BTL) Farmer&#8223;s Association and BTL Women&#8223;s Association. They had set up 
camp outside the university to protest against the forced eviction of approximately 800 families 
from over 400 hectares of land that were inside of the CMU. 
