<p>YEM 3/2011 
<b>Yemen 
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Freedom of 
</b></p>
<p><b>expression;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Human rights 
</b></p>
<p><b>defenders;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Attempted assassination/ reprisals. According to the information received, on 7 July 2011 Mr. 
Ahmed Hashim, Head of the Documentation Department of the Yemeni Organisation for the 
Defence of Democratic Rights and Freedom (Hurryat), was intercepted by two masked men on a 
motorbike, one of whom fired two shots at him with a pistol. The perpetrators reportedly fled the 
scene, crossing a security checkpoint on the way, but were not apprehended by security forces. 
Mr. Hashim did not file a complaint with the police as he feared he might be arrested as a result, 
as has happened to other human right defenders. On 6 July Mr. Hashim and other defnders had 
met with representatives of the OHCHR Assessment Mission regarding alleged human rights 
violations committed by government forces in the context of the repression of protest 
demonstrations. 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
18/07/2011 
JAL 
 
