<p><b>Human rights 
</b></p>
<p><b>defenders;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Detention and allegations of acts of intimidation against residents of the villages located on 
Chhindwada. According to the information received, on 26 June 2011, Mr. Sunilam Mishra, 
National Secretary of the Samajwadi Party and of the Indian Solidarity Committee (INSOCO), 
was arrested by the police and detained incommunicado. He was reportedly told that the cause of 
his arrest was raising slogans and provoking farmers to violence. The police allegedly charged 
farmers inside the village Bhula Mohgaon and arrested 18 villagers. Ms. Aradhna Bhargava, an 
advocate and president of the Women Struggle Committee (Sangharsh Samiti), was also arrested 
and detained for three days. On 22 May 2011, Mr. Mishra and Ms. Bhargava had been attacked 
by around 10 men, after a meeting with farmers, resulting in head injuries and fractures to their 
hands. The investigation into this attack was allegedly not properly conducted. 
</p>
<p>08/08/2011 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
