<p><b>Independence of 
</b></p>
<p><b>judges and 
</b></p>
<p><b>lawyers;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged concerns over fair hearing, insufficiently substantiated suspension and possible removal 
from office of a Judge in the High Court. According to the information received, Mr. Thomas S. 
Masuku, Judge in the High Court of the Kingdom of Swaziland, was notified by letter sent on 28 
June 2011 by the Judicial Service Commission that a formal enquiry on twelve alleged acts of 
misbehaviour had been initiated against him, which may lead to his removal from office. He was 
also invited to attend an oral hearing on his case on 11 August 2011. Another letter dated 30 June 
2011 informed him of his suspension from office until the resolution of the case. Allegedly, most 
allegations are insufficiently substantiated to justify suspension and possible removal from office, 
and the complainants are not clearly identified. Reportedly, the only discernible complainants are 
the Chief Justice and the King of Swaziland.  
</p>
