<p>Alleged forced eviction of more than 3,000 residents in the Hoima district in Uganda.  According 
to the information received, the Ministry of Defense had planned to evict over 3,000 residents 
from seven villages (Kitikara, Ngurwe, Ngoma, Nyakatehe, Kituti, Kabanena and Kasonga) in 
Hoima district, for the purpose of establishing an army base near the oil wells in the region. 
Reportedly, the army base is meant to increase the security in the area. The Ministry of Defense 
reportedly claims ownership over land covering the above mentioned villages.    
