<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Torture;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Violence against 
</b></p>
<p><b>women;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged acts of violence on the basis of allegations of witchcraft. According to the information 
received, Ms. X was accused by her husband of killing his son and two of his brothers as a result 
of sorcery. On 3 October 2009, her husband reportedly publicly assaulted her and accused her of 
sorcery, hitting her repeatedly. Ms. X then allegedly left her house together with her two sons, 
and was rejected by her husband upon her return. In a similar case, Ms. Y was allegedly attacked 
on 7 September 2010 in Wormai village, 10 kms from Kundiwa town in Chimbu province for 
allegedly causing the death of her son through sorcery. Five sons of her husband&#8223;s brother 
</p>
<p>allegedly attacked her and forced a heated knife into her vagina. The case was allegedly reported 
to the police in Kundiawa with no actions taken to bring the alleged perpetrators to justice. 
</p>
