<p>PHL 4/2011 
<b>Philippines 
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Freedom of 
</b></p>
<p><b>expression;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Human rights 
</b></p>
<p><b>defenders;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Summary 
</b></p>
<p><b>executions;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged killing of human rights defender. According to the information received, on 17 October 
2011, Father Fausto Tentorio, an Italian priest and missionary of the Pontifical Institute for 
Foreign Missions (PIME) who had worked in the Philippines since 1978, was shot by an 
unknown man as he was preparing to leave the convent of the Mother of Perpetual Help Parish in 
the Arakan, Cotabato. He was reportedly proclaimed dead on arrival at the hospital as a result of 
multiple gunshot wounds to his head and chest. He had recently been working against the 
expansion of mining activities on tribal lands and had criticized the military for its operations in 
the community. 
</p>
<p>15/12/2011 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 </p>

