<p>Alleged ban of the 2011 Belgrade Pride Parade. According to the information received, in early 
August 2011, the association &#8220;Belgrade Pride Parade&#8221; submitted a written request to the Ministry 
of Interior to hold the 2011 Belgrade Pride Parade on 2 October 2011. In the meantime, peaceful 
counter-protests on 1 and 2 October 2011 were announced. On 30 September 2011, following a 
meeting by the National Security Council, the Minister of Interior announced that all public 
gatherings for the weekend of 1 and 2 October 2011 were banned under article 11(1) of the Law 
on Gathering of Citizens of the Republic of Serbia. 
