<p>Alleged killings of human rights defenders. According to information received Mr. Arpe 
Belayong, the director of the human rights organisation Linundigan and his nephew, Mr. Solte 
San-ogan were killed at the hands of a paramilitary group. It is alleged that two of Mr. 
Belayong&#8223;s minor children were also injured after the attack and currently they are being treated 
for their bullet wounds. Recently, Mr. Belayong had reportedly been particularly active in 
opposing the entry of logging and mining operations in the land of the Higaonon. On 11 October 
2011, it is reported that members of the organisation Linundigan allegedly went into hiding as 
they faced imminent risks of being attacked by the paramilitary forces following the killing of 
Mr. Belayong. 
